member.name: P:SWE1R.Assets.Blocks.ModelBlock.F3DEX2.Vtx.Byte_F
member.summary: In the original asset files, if the vertex has a normal and not a color, the value is always 255. But that is just an indicator. A value somewhere else in the binary structures determines whether the game interprets it as a normal or a color, which means that if you change this value to 255 that does not automatically make the vertex to have a normal instead of a color in the game.
